    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“What news do you bring me?” asks Gaelius. He's attended by master Erebus, his loremaster and advisor.</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts>
        <string>dlgCam(340, 40, 6, 4100);</string>
        <string>dlgTeleportToMarker(TM_DLG_Gaelius_01);</string>
      </onLoadScripts>
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“I found the temple, my Lord.” Tell them everything.</text>
          <def_link>9299</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9297</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“I told you,” says Gaelius, turning to his loremaster, “we should have destroyed it all, leaving no signs that these ruins were ever there. Only then we would have known peace.”

“We did our best,” says Erebus, unfazed. “What happened only underlines that you can’t hide from the past, can’t shove it under a rag and pretend it never happened. I think we should thank this young &lt;man/woman&gt; for coming to you first.”

“You aren’t suggesting...,” says Gaelius.</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>Continue.</text>
          <def_link>9300</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9299</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“You’ve done so much, my Lord,” says Erebus. “What choice do you have now but to keep it – nay, protect it – no matter the cost?”

Gaelius turns to you. “You’ve met this 'god'. What do you think?”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“There is an opportunity in every crisis, my Lord. I have no doubt that you're the man who can seize it.”</text>
          <def_link>9301</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Join him and you'll forge the greatest empire the world has ever known. Oppose him and you'll spend the rest of your days fighting a war you can't win.”</text>
          <def_link>9301</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“As master Erebus said, what choice do you have? The siege was broken. Meru is stronger than ever and his creed spreads fast. You want to give him everything you built? Or put him and those who helped him back in their place?”</text>
          <def_link>9301</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear>aod.gnz_siegeBroken</checkOnAppear>
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9300</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“It’s never that simple,” says Gaelius.</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“It’s not. There is always a price to pay, but think of what you'll gain.”</text>
          <def_link>9302</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Simple or not, it is what's best for House Aurelian, my Lord.”</text>
          <def_link>9302</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Some things are. Either lose to Meru and his zealots or rule supreme over men, bowing only to the living god.”</text>
          <def_link>9304</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear>aod.gnz_siegeBroken</checkOnAppear>
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9301</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“I didn’t build all this just to hand it over when someone – man or god – comes knocking.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“So what do I tell him?”</text>
          <def_link>9303</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9302</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“Tell him that anyone can be killed. Even a god.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“And what would your enemies do while you’re fighting a god out of pride? Would they wait? Would they attack while you’re distracted? Or would they join the god and help him bring you down?”</text>
          <def_link>9328</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“The Magi killed four of them but they had three gods of their own and nearly unlimited resources of a powerful empire. What do you have, my Lord?”</text>
          <def_link>9328</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9303</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“I'm not going to let Meru win,” Gaelius says with determination. “He wants to worship gods? So be it.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“It's a long trip. We'll need an escort.”</text>
          <def_link>9329</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9304</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Gaelius</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Gaelius</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“I don't have a choice, do I?” asks Gaelius, defeated. Erebus looks at you and nods.</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“It's a long trip. We'll need an escort.”</text>
          <def_link>9329</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9328</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“We'll take a few men with us,” nods Gaelius. “Those who proved to be immune to the Call.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“The Call?”</text>
          <def_link>9330</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9329</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“Thousands of people claimed to have heard some Call and left the city,” says Gaelius. “It could be Agathoth, in which case the sooner we make a deal the better.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“I'll need supplies. Can you send for my things?”</text>
          <def_link>9331</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9330</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“They will be brought here shortly. Let me know when you're ready to leave.”</npc_text>
